INSIGHT-From Boeing to Mercedes, a U.S. worker rebellion swells over vaccine mandates
By Tina Bellon and Eric M. Johnson
AUSTIN/SEATTLE, Nov 2 (Reuters) - In Wichita, Kansas, nearly half of the roughly 10,000 employees at aircraft companies Textron Inc and Spirit AeroSystems remain unvaccinated against COVID-19, risking their jobs in defiance of a federal mandate, according to a union official.
"We're going to lose a lot of employees over this," said Cornell Adams, head of the local Machinists union district. Many workers did not object to the vaccines as such, he said, but were staunchly opposed to what they see as government meddling in personal health decisions.
The union district has hired a Texas-based lawyer to assist employees and prepare potential lawsuits against the companies should requests for medical or religious exemptions to vaccination be denied.

_source.body: This is precisely "why" I refuse to donate to the RNC anymore despite the over 2 dozen requests I get nagged with every day.  I find the RNC to be contemptible after yesterday trying to downplay Donald Trump over this past Tuesday shellacing of the DNC.  I do individually support politicians I know who are in agreement with myself.  The Missouri State Rep Nick Schroer about to become Senator, Former Missouri Speaker Tim Jones, Missouri US Senator Joshua Hawley, Missouri AG Eric Schmitt, and a new Montana State Rep possibly here soon.  I know every one of these men personally and every one has stuck their necks out on the line over issues like getting rid of abortions.  We're a pretty tough group but the rest I don't know or have severely let us down.  Most of you know Joshua Hawley and the others are a well developed group ready to proceed with MAGA.  Missouri has toughened up and so is my new home of Montana!  The rest........sheesh......cowards and wimps.
